A set $S$ of distinct positive integers has property bold(N D) if no element
$x$ of $S$ divides the sum of the integers in any subset of $S without {x}$.
Here $S without {x}$ means the set that remains after $x$ is removed from $S$.

#set enum(numbering: "(a)")

+ Find the smallest positive integer $n$ such that ${ 3, 4, n }$ has property
  bold(N D).
+ If $n$ is the number found in (i), prove that no set $S$ with property
  bold(N D) has ${ 3, 4, n }$ as a proper subset.
